<BaseLayout 
  title="About"
  description="Learn more about Denys Korolkov - Senior Frontend Engineer with expertise in React, TypeScript, and modern web development."
>
  <div class="container">
    <article class="about-page">
      <header class="page-header">
        <h1>About Me</h1>
        <p class="page-subtitle">Senior Frontend Engineer passionate about creating exceptional user experiences</p>
      </header>

      <div class="about-content">
        <section class="intro">
          <h2>Hello, I'm Denys</h2>
          <p>
            I'm a highly motivated and result-driven <strong>Frontend Developer</strong> with deep knowledge of full-stack development. 
            Since 2006, I've been professionally crafting digital experiences, and since 2014, I've been successfully working remotely.
          </p>
          <p>
            I have successfully built and delivered numerous web projects from small startups (achieving 500% new user growth in just one year) 
            to large-scale enterprise applications (delivering releases in just 3 months at Groupon) using React, TypeScript, Node.js, and other modern technologies.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="philosophy">
          <h2>My Philosophy</h2>
          <p>
            It's all about having a clear vision of the end-goal and strategic planning. I'm able to select and assign priorities to 
            restricted resources and organize my work to meet tight deadlines. For me, it's very important to stay focused on what 
            truly matters and not get distracted by less important tasks.
          </p>
          <p>
            My personal useful place where I can work and create. I dive into a process fully - it doesn't matter if it's a job or a hobby.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="background">
          <h2>Background</h2>
          <p>
            I was born in Ukraine and grew up in a large family with 4 native siblings and 3 step-siblings. 
            This experience taught me to see the world through different perspectives and gave me strong skills for understanding other people.
          </p>
          <p>
            I believe it's very important when working people are connected by something bigger than just a common idea. 
            I like to be part of a group of like-minded friends, and I feel this connection even when working remotely.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="skills">
          <h2>Technical Expertise</h2>
          <div class="skills-grid">
            <div class="skill-category">
              <h3>Frontend</h3>
